<dl id="n20218e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n20" href="#n20218e">N20 (VI.B.13)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n20all.htm#n20218e"> 218(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Come &amp; see one who / will be the first / tenor in world</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A gentleman who was an enthusiastic lover of music <font color="green">[speaking of Reeve&apos;s performance]</font> said &lsquo;Come and hear a new singer who will be the first tenor in the world.&rsquo; <small> Charles E. Pearce, <a name="CEPS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CEPS"><cite title="source">Sims Reeves: Fifty Years of Music in England</cite></a> (Jun 1924) 59</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
